{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover the latest additions to San Francisco – the system font for Apple platforms – and find out how they can provide more control and versatility when designing interfaces. In addition to weights and optical sizes, San Francisco now supports three new width styles: Condensed, Compressed, and Expanded. We’ll also take you through the linguistic expansion of San Francisco and learn more about the feature-rich Arabic system font families: SF Arabic and SF Arabic Rounded."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc22-110381-meet-the-expanded-san-francisco-font-family"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"Meet the expanded San Francisco font family","roleHeading":"WWDC22"},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Meet-the-family","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Meet the family"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Currently supported","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"SF Pro (default on iOS \/ macOS)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SF Pro Rounded (default on iOS \/ macOS)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"SF Compact (default on watchOS)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SF Compact Rounded (default on watchOS)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SF Mono (for Xcode)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Current weights","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ultralight to Black"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Optical sizes (e.g. 96pt, 70pt, 48pt, 28pt, 12pt)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Today’s focus: “SF Pro”"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple expanded the style in Photos, News and Maps apps"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Explore the new widths","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Explore-the-new-widths"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To weight and optical size, width is now added:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Condensed","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Compressed"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Expanded","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Full overview of all styles:","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/6942160\/173163906-cf9c9b03-6b46-4869-bb54-d3afca115efe.png"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Styles towards center have more neutral voice","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Outside ones more expressive and stronger voice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Choosing & pairing fonts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All styles provide same language support","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Vertical proportions are always the same for all","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Stem thickness stays relatively the same","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Regular: Is best to read, default to this"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Condensed: Comfortable width, but fit more text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Compressed: Very densed proportions, nice as a display style","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Expanded: Use on smaller labels and secondary content"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Either you can save space, or use larger size with same space","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Don’t use “Compressed” for long texts due to bad legibility"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example combinations:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Photos app combines Compressed Semibold for Title, Expanded Bold for Subtitle","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A world of possible combinations:"}]}]}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/6942160\/173163915-f9884e76-e2ab-4c51-be10-b0b98b011a74.png"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"News app uses Condensed or Compressed for title to fit more in, giving the title personality","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Expanded used for author"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Maps app uses expanded for long mountains to fill greater space, for example"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Recap:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Space efficiency"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Reinforce hierarchies","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Expressive display styles"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Latin, Greek, and Cyrillic supported","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Welcome SF Arabic","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Welcome-SF-Arabic"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Extending the linguistic coverage of San Francisco, started last year"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"SF Arabic introduced last year, features full gamut of weights","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/6942160\/173163935-7fa777f0-379a-4dd6-9f2e-9a6224fd70c4.png","type":"image"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Optical sizes are tailored for Arabic, fine-tuned for legibility","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Many extras like vocals and Quranic notations added","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"New this year: SF Arabic Rounded","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fonts are available for download on Apple Developer Website"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Written By","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Written-By"},{"columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"Jeehut","type":"image"}]}]},{"size":4,"content":[{"level":3,"text":"Cihat Gündüz","type":"heading","anchor":"Cihat-Gündüz"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[